sec-IsHTMLDDA-internal-slot.title: #sec-IsHTMLDDA-internal-slot The [[IsHTMLDDA]] Internal Slot
sec-IsHTMLDDA-internal-slot.html:
#sec-IsHTMLDDA-internal-slot The [[IsHTMLDDA]] Internal Slot

An [[IsHTMLDDA]] internal slot may exist on host-defined objects. Objects with an [[IsHTMLDDA]] internal slot behave like undefined in the ToBoolean and Abstract Equality Comparison abstract operations and when used as an operand for the typeof operator.

Note

Objects with an [[IsHTMLDDA]] internal slot are never created by this specification. However, the document.all object in web browsers is a host-defined exotic object with this slot that exists for web compatibility purposes. There are no other known examples of this type of object and implementations should not create any with the exception of document.all.

sec-assignmenttargettype-lefthandsideexp.title: #sec-assignmenttargettype-lefthandsideexpression-callexpression-arguments-invalid AssignmentTargetType of LeftHandSideExpression : CallExpression
sec-assignmenttargettype-lefthandsideexp.html:
#sec-assignmenttargettype-lefthandsideexpression-callexpression-arguments-invalid AssignmentTargetType of LeftHandSideExpression : CallExpression

The following Runtime Semantics rules are appended to the content of subclause #sec-assignment-operators-runtime-semantics-evaluation:

AssignmentExpression:LeftHandSideExpression
  1. If AssignmentTargetType of LeftHandSideExpression is not simple and occurs in non-strict code, throw a ReferenceError exception.
AssignmentExpression:LeftHandSideExpressionAssignmentOperatorAssignmentExpression
  1. If AssignmentTargetType of LeftHandSideExpression is not simple and occurs in non-strict code, throw a ReferenceError exception.
